  <!-- Grid Section -->
  <section id="books" class="container-fluid py-5">
    <div class="row g-4 mb-4 mb-md-5">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/6280209210" target="_blank"><img src="assets/images/The_Kingdom_of_Jamus_2025_Cover.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="The Kingdom of Jamus"></a>
        <p class="truncate">Jamus is the king of the Kingdom of Jamus, and as king, he does whatever he wants to do. He
          reigns supreme, declaring wrong to be right and right to be wrong. But as the truth about his kingdom is
          revealed, he is forced to confront the limits of his power and learn to trust in someone greater than
          himself.<br />

          The Kingdom of Jamus is a tale of rebellion, the struggle for control, and the journey toward surrender and
          trust, showing the importance of humility and the freedom that comes with letting go.</p>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/6280209210" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-4">
       <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/6280209717" target="_blank"><img src="assets/images/Haircuts_For_Sheep_2025_Cover.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="Haircuts For Sheep"></a>
        <p class="truncate">A flock of sheep, lured by a stranger’s promises of fortune and fame, foolishly allow him to
          shear their precious wool. Only then do they realize that their wool was more valuable than any riches, and
          that something beyond material wealth is needed to fill the void left by their loss.<br>

          With roots as deep as the Garden of Eden, Haircuts for Sheep is a story of deception, repentance and
          redemption.</p>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/6280209717" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-4">
       <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/6280209628" target="_blank"><img src="assets/images/Jamus_Nose_Is_Too_Big_2025_Cover.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="Jamus' Nose is Too Too Big"></a>
        <p class="truncate">Jamus has a special nose, a unique nose, a nose that is one of a kind, but he struggles to
          believe it when everyone around him points and gawks at its “too too big” size. He begins to wonder—are they
          right? Is there something wrong with him, or has he let their hurtful words create an image of himself that
          isn’t quite true? <br />

          This quirky story blends wit with touching moments of reflection, encouraging readers to embrace their
